ReviewText: Not a cream concealer. Doesn’t have anything creamy in it. I bought it because I have dry skin and saw so many good reviews. Tried everything, blended with finger, with beauty blender, with brush, even sprayed setting spray to blender and on top of it before blending, but nothing worked. Cakes immediately WHILE APPLYING. I always keep my under eyes moisturized and even tried different eye creams to sit under it, but no luck. If you have under eyes like me (dry that needs to be moisturized with belif aqua bomb and skinfix 360 cream at night),skip this. The coverage is medium on my face.
ContextDataValues/IncentivizedReview/Dim: I received this product as a free sample
Title: Not for dry skin. Cakes immediately.

ReviewText: Love this concealer highly pigmented great for covering up imperfections like pimples, sun damage, any discoloration really. This isn’t an under eye concealer this is a perfecting concealer. I love to use it to carve out my eyebrows. I do my eye makeup before my base so this with a concealer brush allows me to get that perfected even base, all the way right close to the brows. Because lines of demarcation aren’t cute.

ReviewText: Covers well, used to be erase paste. No. 1 has a slight pinkish that is great for dark circles. Shade No. works well when I have more color in the summer. Soft, lightweight. I often only brighten your with only moisturizer this and a good mascara. Quick and easy.

ReviewText: This is the second best thing to Benefit’s previous hydrating concealer (bring that back!!). I have mature dry skin and this is the only concealer I can count on to look normal and not cakey. I just dab with my finger and pat in lightly.

Title: Works for me!

ReviewText:
So this is a PSA for a similar product, Boi-ing Brightening Concealer no 4.  I picked the concealer up on Benefits site to get free shipping. 
The shade is much deeper and peachier than the swatch so just be aware that the Brightening concealer is not a one and done but should be layered with another product. Just wasn’t what I was looking for this summer. 
It’s also very emollient so it might work best paired with a matte concealer or it might melt off.
ContextDataValues/IncentivizedReview/Dim: I received this product as a free sample
